1
00:00:25,080 --> 00:00:26,610
Haejun, what are you doing?

2
00:00:27,990 --> 00:00:29,540
Nothing much.

3
00:00:29,820 --> 00:00:31,270
I'm painting.

4
00:00:32,930 --> 00:00:34,930
We haven't seen each other for days.

5
00:00:35,360 --> 00:00:36,430
Don't you miss me?

6
00:00:37,710 --> 00:00:38,610
I do.

7
00:00:40,230 --> 00:00:42,080
But we just met two days ago.

8
00:00:45,210 --> 00:00:46,270
Come on.

9
00:00:46,490 --> 00:00:48,680
I miss you even when I don't see you
only for a day.

10
00:00:48,680 --> 00:00:50,010
All I think about is you—

11
00:00:50,200 --> 00:00:51,960
I can't do anything else.

12
00:00:52,980 --> 00:00:53,960
Well,

13
00:00:54,650 --> 00:00:56,050
shall we meet tomorrow?

14
00:00:56,660 --> 00:00:58,720
I need to go get my report card.

15
00:00:59,050 --> 00:01:00,670
I don't want to go alone.

16
00:01:02,580 --> 00:01:03,930
Your report card?

17
00:01:04,930 --> 00:01:06,050
What should I do?

18
00:01:06,890 --> 00:01:09,430
Something came up
and I need to go somewhere.

19
00:01:12,220 --> 00:01:13,570
So suddenly?

20
00:01:14,280 --> 00:01:15,430
Where are you going?

21
00:01:16,730 --> 00:01:18,430
Did something happen?

22
00:01:18,920 --> 00:01:20,180
It's nothing serious.

23
00:01:20,460 --> 00:01:21,960
I have to go now,

24
00:01:22,280 --> 00:01:24,080
to meet an old friend.

25
00:01:24,960 --> 00:01:26,010
I'll be away...

26
00:01:26,700 --> 00:01:28,700
for about a week—

27
00:01:29,160 --> 00:01:30,680
it might be even longer.

28
00:01:31,830 --> 00:01:32,759
Then...

29
00:01:34,229 --> 00:01:36,090
you'll be away for Christmas too?

30
00:01:40,460 --> 00:01:41,810
Got it.

31
00:01:43,090 --> 00:01:44,280
Take care.

32
00:01:51,200 --> 00:01:52,670
What was I expecting?

33
00:01:53,740 --> 00:01:55,800
Christmas is just around the corner.

34
00:02:07,680 --> 00:02:09,680
Hello, Mr. Kim Haejun.

35
00:02:10,570 --> 00:02:12,000
I'm Kim Haejun.

36
00:02:28,900 --> 00:02:31,340
[Score: C, C, B, D, D]

37
00:02:32,890 --> 00:02:33,560
Gosh.

38
00:02:37,800 --> 00:02:38,460
Seriously.

39
00:02:46,240 --> 00:02:47,100
Hello, Professor.

40
00:02:47,100 --> 00:02:50,440
You came in last in this final exam.

41
00:02:50,440 --> 00:02:53,800
This'll affect your graduation.
Your mom will be worried too.

42
00:02:53,800 --> 00:02:57,130
There will be online classes in winter,
so sign up for those.

43
00:02:58,460 --> 00:02:59,480
Okay, thank you.

44
00:03:00,230 --> 00:03:01,240
I'll study hard.

45
00:03:19,910 --> 00:03:22,140
If you say useless things like that again,

46
00:03:22,140 --> 00:03:24,140
I'll only give you iced Americano.

47
00:03:48,900 --> 00:03:52,360
[Jaehun]

48
00:03:55,480 --> 00:04:04,720
[What do you think? Is it pretty?]

49
00:04:16,399 --> 00:04:18,240
He will come, right?

50
00:04:38,550 --> 00:04:42,280
I want to spend Christmas together
with him in a house like this too.

51
00:05:00,960 --> 00:05:02,450
♪ Jingle bells, jingle bells ♪

52
00:05:02,450 --> 00:05:03,750
Merry Christmas!

53
00:05:04,010 --> 00:05:05,570
You didn't expect me to come, did you?

54
00:05:05,570 --> 00:05:06,730
Are you at home alone?

55
00:05:06,730 --> 00:05:07,530
Soyu.

56
00:05:07,820 --> 00:05:09,680
Why are you here?

57
00:05:09,780 --> 00:05:11,700
Can't I just come?

58
00:05:11,710 --> 00:05:13,710
Or is there someone at home?

59
00:05:14,280 --> 00:05:16,190
No, that's not it.

60
00:05:17,150 --> 00:05:19,930
That's great then, if you're alone.

61
00:05:20,980 --> 00:05:23,930
I missed you so much today.

62
00:05:23,940 --> 00:05:25,720
You didn't reply to my messages,

63
00:05:25,720 --> 00:05:27,120
and I was worried you weren't home.

64
00:05:27,120 --> 00:05:28,910
So I kept having bad thoughts.

65
00:05:34,010 --> 00:05:34,680
Ta-da!

66
00:05:35,560 --> 00:05:36,960
How is it? Not bad, right?

67
00:05:37,190 --> 00:05:40,200
When I put this on, I was thinking

68
00:05:40,250 --> 00:05:43,490
if you would say I look pretty in it.

69
00:05:43,820 --> 00:05:44,590
It's pretty.

70
00:05:45,650 --> 00:05:46,350
But...

71
00:05:48,800 --> 00:05:49,800
aren't you cold?

72
00:05:50,350 --> 00:05:50,930
No.

73
00:05:50,930 --> 00:05:51,530
It's fine.

74
00:05:51,650 --> 00:05:53,350
As long as I can show it

75
00:05:53,350 --> 00:05:54,150
to you.

76
00:05:56,560 --> 00:05:57,710
This is a gift.

77
00:05:57,710 --> 00:06:00,430
I bought it with the money
I earned from my part-time job.

78
00:06:00,430 --> 00:06:03,830
I just don't want you
to receive this from others.

79
00:06:13,550 --> 00:06:14,410
I can't take it.

80
00:06:14,800 --> 00:06:16,070
Please just take it.

81
00:06:16,080 --> 00:06:17,820
Don't feel burdened.

82
00:06:18,050 --> 00:06:18,750
It's just

83
00:06:19,270 --> 00:06:21,270
a gift, nothing else.

84
00:06:25,480 --> 00:06:27,480
I came today for a reason.

85
00:06:28,770 --> 00:06:30,220
My birthday is in a few days,

86
00:06:30,220 --> 00:06:32,220
and Christmas is coming too.

87
00:06:32,220 --> 00:06:35,220
So I wanted to ask you this:

88
00:06:35,580 --> 00:06:37,060
Haejun,

89
00:06:37,360 --> 00:06:39,800
can you spend this Christmas with me?

90
00:06:42,390 --> 00:06:44,330
You don't have to answer me right away.

91
00:06:44,330 --> 00:06:45,060
I just

92
00:06:45,550 --> 00:06:48,110
hope you can understand how sincere

93
00:06:48,540 --> 00:06:50,260
my feelings are for you.

94
00:06:53,250 --> 00:06:54,020
Contact me.

95
00:06:54,400 --> 00:06:54,970
It's fine if it's short

96
00:06:54,970 --> 00:06:57,530
or a rejection—

97
00:06:58,360 --> 00:07:00,360
no, it's not fine—

98
00:07:01,810 --> 00:07:03,540
but I'll wait for your message.

99
00:07:23,050 --> 00:07:24,790
Are you Kim Haejun?

100
00:07:26,010 --> 00:07:27,170
Merry Christmas.

101
00:07:50,210 --> 00:07:50,600
[I'm sorry, Haejun. Something came up,
so I can't celebrate Christmas
with you today.
This is your gift for you.]

102
00:07:50,600 --> 00:07:51,659
I'm sorry, Haejun.

103
00:07:51,900 --> 00:07:53,170
Something came up,

104
00:07:53,780 --> 00:07:56,380
so I can't celebrate Christmas
with you today.

105
00:07:56,500 --> 00:07:57,700
This is a gift for you.

106
00:08:01,210 --> 00:08:02,030
What's this?

107
00:08:13,520 --> 00:08:15,920
Don't make promises
if you can't keep them.

108
00:08:17,210 --> 00:08:18,940
He's ignoring all my texts too.

109
00:08:21,410 --> 00:08:22,810
Am I being too sensitive?

110
00:08:44,560 --> 00:08:45,460
Haejun!

111
00:08:50,540 --> 00:08:51,790
Haejun!

112
00:09:03,790 --> 00:09:07,730
[Will you spend Christmas with me?]

113
00:09:13,510 --> 00:09:16,730
[Yes or yes]

114
00:09:33,960 --> 00:09:35,560
I thought you wouldn't come.

115
00:10:31,110 --> 00:10:32,180
Gift for you.

116
00:10:35,140 --> 00:10:35,870
Isn't it pretty?

117
00:10:35,870 --> 00:10:36,500
Yes.

118
00:10:38,180 --> 00:10:40,380
I thought you wouldn't come back today.

119
00:10:43,540 --> 00:10:45,270
I wanted to give you a surprise.

120
00:10:46,220 --> 00:10:47,750
You are the easiest to fool.

121
00:10:49,190 --> 00:10:50,820
Is it that fun to fool me?

122
00:10:54,130 --> 00:10:55,430
Don't be angry.

123
00:10:56,460 --> 00:10:57,860
Pack your luggage today.

124
00:10:58,960 --> 00:11:00,890
I'll take you somewhere tomorrow.

125
00:11:02,090 --> 00:11:02,540
We are

126
00:11:03,180 --> 00:11:04,180
going somewhere?

127
00:11:06,140 --> 00:11:07,120
Is it Firenze?

128
00:11:08,190 --> 00:11:10,110
I don't have a passport,

129
00:11:10,440 --> 00:11:12,170
nor do I have a visa yet, though?

130
00:11:13,920 --> 00:11:14,860
We can go there

131
00:11:16,040 --> 00:11:16,840
in the future.

132
00:11:17,570 --> 00:11:18,140
Also...

133
00:11:19,820 --> 00:11:21,550
the place we're going tomorrow

134
00:11:21,550 --> 00:11:22,980
is not that far.

135
00:11:24,230 --> 00:11:25,230
I'll tell you

136
00:11:25,730 --> 00:11:27,260
when we get there tomorrow.

137
00:11:27,270 --> 00:11:28,270
When we get there,

138
00:11:29,410 --> 00:11:30,470
we will be together

139
00:11:30,650 --> 00:11:31,930
throughout

140
00:11:32,220 --> 00:11:33,520
the whole time.

141
00:11:40,830 --> 00:11:41,280
Hyung.

142
00:11:43,750 --> 00:11:45,950
Aren't you going to sleep here tonight?

143
00:12:07,250 --> 00:12:10,050
It's my first time
going on a trip to somewhere far.

144
00:12:11,220 --> 00:12:13,090
You haven't been on many trips?

145
00:12:14,440 --> 00:12:17,450
From elementary school to college,

146
00:12:18,900 --> 00:12:21,050
I stayed in the same area.

147
00:12:22,400 --> 00:12:23,630
I was thinking of going

148
00:12:23,630 --> 00:12:25,880
to a university in a different region,

149
00:12:26,990 --> 00:12:29,660
but my mom got sick,
and I couldn't leave.

150
00:12:32,940 --> 00:12:36,030
You're not disappointed that
you're going on a trip with me, right?

151
00:12:36,030 --> 00:12:36,830
Of course not.

152
00:12:38,040 --> 00:12:39,570
I'm glad I'm going with you.

153
00:12:40,960 --> 00:12:41,550
So...

154
00:12:42,800 --> 00:12:43,860
where are we going?

155
00:12:45,900 --> 00:12:46,640
To a place

156
00:12:48,030 --> 00:12:49,230
where no one knows us.

157
00:13:28,060 --> 00:13:31,790
I want to spend Christmas together
with him in a house like this too.

158
00:13:35,450 --> 00:13:36,780
Why are you spacing out?

159
00:13:39,620 --> 00:13:40,420
Do you like it?

160
00:13:41,900 --> 00:13:43,960
Are we going to spend Christmas here?

161
00:13:44,160 --> 00:13:45,160
Just the two of us?

162
00:13:46,090 --> 00:13:46,540
Yes.

163
00:13:47,320 --> 00:13:47,770
Why?

164
00:13:48,310 --> 00:13:49,310
You don't like it?

165
00:13:50,190 --> 00:13:50,810
No.

166
00:13:51,920 --> 00:13:53,380
It just doesn't feel real.

167
00:13:57,060 --> 00:13:58,260
This is the resort

168
00:13:58,800 --> 00:14:00,080
my mom left me.

169
00:14:01,760 --> 00:14:04,160
I have someone
to take care of it regularly.

170
00:14:04,530 --> 00:14:06,860
Whenever I want to be alone,
I'd come here.

171
00:14:10,980 --> 00:14:11,970
Your mother

172
00:14:13,760 --> 00:14:15,460
must be a warm person.

173
00:14:21,490 --> 00:14:22,420
Close your eyes.

174
00:14:35,840 --> 00:14:36,840
What do you think?

175
00:14:37,550 --> 00:14:38,480
Isn't it pretty?

176
00:14:39,930 --> 00:14:40,530
What is...

177
00:14:41,010 --> 00:14:41,500
this?

178
00:14:43,130 --> 00:14:43,950
An ankle cuff.

179
00:14:45,220 --> 00:14:46,150
Isn't it pretty?

180
00:14:47,250 --> 00:14:48,030
Is it a gift?

181
00:14:48,690 --> 00:14:49,480
Yes.

182
00:14:53,120 --> 00:14:53,900
Wait.

183
00:15:04,230 --> 00:15:05,490
After putting this on,

184
00:15:06,150 --> 00:15:07,480
no matter where you are,

185
00:15:08,260 --> 00:15:09,120
or where you go,

186
00:15:11,160 --> 00:15:12,520
I will know.

187
00:15:15,560 --> 00:15:16,740
Isn't it weird?

188
00:15:17,320 --> 00:15:17,920
Not at all.

189
00:15:19,180 --> 00:15:20,180
I think it's sexy.

190
00:15:22,520 --> 00:15:23,190
But...

191
00:15:24,100 --> 00:15:26,100
it'll be inconvenient when I go out.

192
00:15:28,630 --> 00:15:29,270
Go out?

193
00:15:31,520 --> 00:15:32,780
Where do you want to go?

194
00:15:35,400 --> 00:15:36,930
No, that's not what I meant.

195
00:16:00,680 --> 00:16:01,880
Wherever you go,

196
00:16:03,000 --> 00:16:04,150
or whoever you meet,

197
00:16:05,950 --> 00:16:07,750
you must stay in my line of sight,

198
00:16:09,730 --> 00:16:10,310
got it?

199
00:16:11,580 --> 00:16:12,110
Yes.

200
00:16:17,150 --> 00:16:17,910
Good boy.

201
00:16:37,640 --> 00:16:38,700
Hello, Professor.

202
00:16:42,100 --> 00:16:43,500
Yes, I got the documents.

203
00:16:45,160 --> 00:16:46,360
Yes, I'll study hard.

204
00:16:48,650 --> 00:16:49,940
Yes, I'll study hard.

205
00:16:51,160 --> 00:16:51,790
Yes.

206
00:16:55,210 --> 00:16:58,940
Your school is still reaching out to you
even though it's vacation?

207
00:16:59,810 --> 00:17:00,570
Actually,

208
00:17:03,010 --> 00:17:05,069
there's something I didn't tell you.

209
00:17:07,349 --> 00:17:08,730
My grades were not good,

210
00:17:10,230 --> 00:17:13,490
so I have to attend online classes
during winter vacation.

211
00:17:22,690 --> 00:17:24,550
So you're a problematic student.

212
00:17:24,920 --> 00:17:25,849
That's not true.

213
00:17:27,650 --> 00:17:28,329
Hand.

214
00:17:31,360 --> 00:17:32,090
Come with me.

215
00:17:36,010 --> 00:17:37,070
Where are we going?

216
00:17:51,890 --> 00:17:53,890
Did your mother like painting too?

217
00:17:55,180 --> 00:17:57,240
This is the studio I prepared for you.

218
00:17:57,710 --> 00:17:59,240
I thought you might need it.

219
00:17:59,810 --> 00:18:01,360
Paint whatever you want.

220
00:18:02,520 --> 00:18:03,590
It's great!

221
00:18:03,950 --> 00:18:06,250
The paint is new and the frame is new too.

222
00:18:06,930 --> 00:18:09,190
You must have prepared it
for a long time.

223
00:18:09,580 --> 00:18:10,330
How is it?

224
00:18:11,190 --> 00:18:12,070
Do you like it?

225
00:18:13,720 --> 00:18:14,920
It feels like a dream.

226
00:18:17,600 --> 00:18:19,030
Does me being nice to you

227
00:18:19,520 --> 00:18:20,870
feel that unreal?

228
00:18:21,920 --> 00:18:22,670
It's just...

229
00:18:24,520 --> 00:18:26,590
difficult to believe.

230
00:18:28,760 --> 00:18:29,560
Even so,

231
00:18:30,460 --> 00:18:32,280
it's important

232
00:18:32,850 --> 00:18:34,800
that I appear in your dream, right?

233
00:18:35,050 --> 00:18:36,050
Even so,

234
00:18:36,620 --> 00:18:38,950
you should appear
a lot in my real life too.

235
00:18:41,830 --> 00:18:44,030
I need a few more plaster statues.

236
00:18:45,740 --> 00:18:46,740
Plaster statues?

237
00:18:50,030 --> 00:18:50,960
You have me.

238
00:18:51,980 --> 00:18:53,770
Why do you need plaster statues?

239
00:18:53,770 --> 00:18:54,570
Do...

240
00:18:54,970 --> 00:18:57,100
Do you still think I'm not good enough?

241
00:18:57,220 --> 00:18:58,520
No.

242
00:18:59,790 --> 00:19:02,090
If I paint you, I'll be shy.

243
00:19:02,390 --> 00:19:03,850
And you're so busy.

244
00:19:07,060 --> 00:19:07,910
Come here.

245
00:19:12,990 --> 00:19:14,570
Don't feel burdened.

246
00:19:15,860 --> 00:19:18,990
I don't do things like this
to ask for anything in return.

247
00:19:20,800 --> 00:19:21,470
Still...

248
00:19:23,450 --> 00:19:25,570
I don't know how to repay you.

249
00:19:27,260 --> 00:19:28,950
There's no need.

250
00:19:31,050 --> 00:19:32,200
I only want

251
00:19:33,080 --> 00:19:34,700
you to listen to me.

252
00:19:35,740 --> 00:19:36,470
Understand?

253
00:19:55,470 --> 00:19:56,190
Yes.

254
00:19:56,460 --> 00:19:57,660
Hey, Han Jaehun.

255
00:19:58,390 --> 00:19:59,490
Don't you miss me?

256
00:20:00,250 --> 00:20:02,890
We met not long ago. What's up?

257
00:20:03,810 --> 00:20:06,980
Must there be a reason for me to call you?

258
00:20:08,100 --> 00:20:09,230
I'm in Seoul.

259
00:20:09,680 --> 00:20:11,480
I'm going to stay here for a while.

260
00:20:11,480 --> 00:20:12,550
You're not...

261
00:20:13,220 --> 00:20:16,080
asking me to help you
look for a place to stay, right?

262
00:20:16,560 --> 00:20:18,090
That's nothing difficult.

263
00:20:18,400 --> 00:20:20,200
Why don't we just live together?

264
00:20:20,450 --> 00:20:21,600
Just kidding.

265
00:20:22,990 --> 00:20:24,370
Do you want to grab a drink?

266
00:20:24,370 --> 00:20:25,370
Where are you?

267
00:20:25,880 --> 00:20:27,080
Same old place.

268
00:20:27,740 --> 00:20:29,540
I heard there are many new faces.

269
00:20:29,720 --> 00:20:31,250
Let's meet today.

270
00:20:32,880 --> 00:20:34,340
Okay, I'll be right there.

271
00:20:46,760 --> 00:20:47,470
Are you

272
00:20:47,470 --> 00:20:48,400
going out?

273
00:20:48,740 --> 00:20:49,870
Who are you meeting?

274
00:20:51,480 --> 00:20:53,060
I'm just meeting a friend.

275
00:20:54,010 --> 00:20:55,410
When are you coming back?

276
00:20:58,810 --> 00:20:59,880
It's a secret.

277
00:21:01,900 --> 00:21:03,120
It won't be late.

278
00:21:03,420 --> 00:21:05,880
There's food in the fridge
if you're hungry.

279
00:21:07,050 --> 00:21:07,850
Okay.

280
00:21:10,490 --> 00:21:11,890
Don't eat bread with jam.

281
00:21:12,160 --> 00:21:13,210
You've gained weight.

282
00:21:13,210 --> 00:21:14,360
Got it.

283
00:21:15,760 --> 00:21:16,690
I'm heading off.

284
00:21:17,190 --> 00:21:17,990
Give me a kiss.

285
00:21:21,290 --> 00:21:21,940
No need.

286
00:21:21,940 --> 00:21:22,670
I'm leaving.

287
00:21:23,490 --> 00:21:25,040
Go ahead. Come home early.

288
00:21:32,410 --> 00:21:32,940
[Minwoo]

289
00:21:38,950 --> 00:21:40,400
Minwoo, it's me.

290
00:21:40,940 --> 00:21:41,940
I'm back in Korea.

291
00:21:43,100 --> 00:21:45,920
Aren't you with Jaehun?

292
00:21:46,250 --> 00:21:48,310
I thought you were already together.

293
00:21:50,150 --> 00:21:52,700
Okay, I'll stop teasing you.

294
00:21:53,930 --> 00:21:55,640
I'm meeting Jaehun today.

295
00:21:56,290 --> 00:21:58,220
I'll get some information for you.

296
00:21:58,780 --> 00:21:59,850
Okay.

297
00:22:05,460 --> 00:22:06,960
Han Jaehun.

298
00:22:07,570 --> 00:22:09,630
I hope you're just as you were before.

299
00:22:34,820 --> 00:22:35,700
Jaehun's size

300
00:22:36,480 --> 00:22:38,540
is similar to mine.

301
00:22:42,230 --> 00:22:46,560
Putting them together like this feels like
we are living together—it's nice.

302
00:22:54,430 --> 00:22:55,330
But...

303
00:22:56,600 --> 00:22:58,570
Jaehun has friends?

304
00:23:00,100 --> 00:23:01,960
What kind of person would they be?

305
00:23:24,090 --> 00:23:25,880
Do you have to get married?

306
00:23:27,310 --> 00:23:27,860
Okay.

307
00:23:29,530 --> 00:23:30,530
Okay, got it.

308
00:23:31,700 --> 00:23:33,210
Of course I support you.

309
00:23:37,160 --> 00:23:38,500
I'll call you later.

310
00:23:39,630 --> 00:23:40,400
You're here.

311
00:23:46,600 --> 00:23:47,460
Here.

312
00:23:51,760 --> 00:23:52,760
I can do it myself.

313
00:24:00,670 --> 00:24:02,770
Why didn't you bring
your partner today?

314
00:24:02,770 --> 00:24:04,050
Are you abstaining

315
00:24:04,690 --> 00:24:06,290
or becoming a monk?

316
00:24:07,840 --> 00:24:09,740
Will someone who is becoming a monk

317
00:24:09,740 --> 00:24:10,890
come drink with you?

318
00:24:21,050 --> 00:24:21,950
You

319
00:24:22,620 --> 00:24:24,720
look different from before.

320
00:24:26,120 --> 00:24:26,820
How so?

321
00:24:30,100 --> 00:24:32,030
Well, how do I put this?

322
00:24:32,600 --> 00:24:34,400
You look more alive than before.

323
00:24:35,950 --> 00:24:36,970
People change.

324
00:24:39,640 --> 00:24:42,370
I didn't expect you
to be saying things like that.

325
00:24:44,350 --> 00:24:46,250
Was I that cold before?

326
00:24:46,250 --> 00:24:47,120
No.

327
00:24:47,930 --> 00:24:50,190
You're just more boring than in the past.

328
00:24:56,090 --> 00:24:56,820
Speaking of,

329
00:24:57,840 --> 00:25:01,050
you were overseas for a long time—
why come back so suddenly?

330
00:25:01,050 --> 00:25:02,580
Would you believe me if I say

331
00:25:02,650 --> 00:25:03,510
it's to see you?

332
00:25:11,400 --> 00:25:14,130
Aren't you afraid that
I'll poison that alcohol?

333
00:25:17,320 --> 00:25:20,320
If you wanted to poison me,
you'd have done so long ago.

334
00:25:20,470 --> 00:25:21,930
Why wait till now?

335
00:25:22,840 --> 00:25:23,920
You really know me.

336
00:25:26,670 --> 00:25:28,060
I've been busy.

337
00:25:28,410 --> 00:25:30,180
I don't have time to play with you.

338
00:25:30,180 --> 00:25:31,440
What are you busy with?

339
00:25:31,680 --> 00:25:33,210
Picking your next partner?

340
00:25:38,040 --> 00:25:39,300
I'm in a relationship.

341
00:25:40,630 --> 00:25:41,690
With that fiancee?

342
00:25:42,450 --> 00:25:43,030
No.

343
00:25:44,580 --> 00:25:46,300
There's someone I like.

344
00:25:47,280 --> 00:25:49,200
We are seriously dating.

345
00:25:51,390 --> 00:25:52,160
You?

346
00:25:52,160 --> 00:25:52,990
Dating?

347
00:25:54,690 --> 00:25:55,650
My gosh.

348
00:25:56,190 --> 00:25:58,390
I didn't expect you to become like this.

349
00:26:00,460 --> 00:26:02,030
I told you people change.

350
00:26:07,900 --> 00:26:08,470
Here.

351
00:26:08,990 --> 00:26:10,450
Cheers to your great love.

352
00:26:22,900 --> 00:26:24,170
Love

353
00:26:24,170 --> 00:26:25,630
is really a magical thing.

354
00:26:26,070 --> 00:26:27,930
You look much better than before.

355
00:26:28,490 --> 00:26:30,090
What kind of person are they?

356
00:26:35,800 --> 00:26:36,600
They're a cute

357
00:26:37,820 --> 00:26:38,590
person.

358
00:27:11,550 --> 00:27:13,200
When is Jaehun coming back?

359
00:27:20,300 --> 00:27:21,880
Haejun!

360
00:27:22,720 --> 00:27:23,290
Hyung.

361
00:27:25,240 --> 00:27:26,820
Why did you drink so much?

362
00:27:28,040 --> 00:27:29,050
Are you Haejun?

363
00:27:30,880 --> 00:27:31,940
What are you doing?

364
00:27:31,970 --> 00:27:32,700
I missed you.

365
00:27:34,130 --> 00:27:35,260
Why are you still up?

366
00:27:37,650 --> 00:27:38,810
You missed me?

367
00:27:39,340 --> 00:27:40,490
My baby.

368
00:27:42,170 --> 00:27:43,830
Yes, I didn't sleep.

369
00:27:44,050 --> 00:27:45,600
Why did you drink so much?

370
00:27:45,600 --> 00:27:46,860
Did something happen?

371
00:27:51,600 --> 00:27:53,530
You're wearing the bell I gave you.

372
00:27:55,420 --> 00:27:56,280
Let me touch it.

373
00:27:57,540 --> 00:27:58,100
Hyung!

374
00:27:58,420 --> 00:27:59,380
Are you okay?

375
00:28:01,160 --> 00:28:02,690
Get up and get changed.

376
00:28:02,920 --> 00:28:03,820
Get up.

377
00:28:04,980 --> 00:28:06,470
Why are you so heavy?

378
00:28:06,470 --> 00:28:07,270
Gosh.

379
00:28:19,070 --> 00:28:20,090
I'm exhausted.

380
00:28:21,760 --> 00:28:22,570
Let me

381
00:28:22,820 --> 00:28:24,340
get him changed first.

382
00:28:28,330 --> 00:28:29,420
Kim Haejun.

383
00:28:30,970 --> 00:28:33,200
Kiss me, okay?

384
00:28:33,930 --> 00:28:35,880
It's uncomfortable to sleep in this.

385
00:28:35,880 --> 00:28:38,340
Get changed into something clean
and sleep.

386
00:28:41,800 --> 00:28:42,760
Haejun.

387
00:28:44,320 --> 00:28:45,830
Don't leave me, okay?

388
00:28:46,140 --> 00:28:47,750
Don't leave me.

389
00:28:47,780 --> 00:28:49,380
I won't allow you to leave me!

390
00:28:50,120 --> 00:28:51,950
You can't leave me.

391
00:28:53,110 --> 00:28:54,240
I won't abandon you.

392
00:28:54,810 --> 00:28:56,140
I'm not going anywhere.

393
00:29:28,590 --> 00:29:29,550
Kim Haejun!

394
00:30:11,610 --> 00:30:12,420
No! No!

395
00:30:17,090 --> 00:30:18,050
No!

396
00:30:22,180 --> 00:30:22,790
All right.

397
00:30:23,310 --> 00:30:25,020
No, I have to go.

398
00:30:25,770 --> 00:30:27,310
Haejun is waiting for me.

399
00:30:27,330 --> 00:30:27,990
I have to go.

400
00:30:28,940 --> 00:30:31,070
I'll take you home. Let's go together.

401
00:30:31,450 --> 00:30:32,150
Not there.

402
00:30:32,880 --> 00:30:33,740
Let's go there.

403
00:30:44,760 --> 00:30:45,720
He's changed

404
00:30:46,310 --> 00:30:47,770
a lot more than I expected.

405
00:31:08,520 --> 00:31:09,750
Yes, sir.

406
00:31:11,140 --> 00:31:11,980
Don't worry.

407
00:31:13,060 --> 00:31:15,050
I'll take care of your fiance.

408
00:31:15,930 --> 00:31:18,630
I'll make him cut ties with that guy.

409
00:31:19,800 --> 00:31:20,880
In that case,

410
00:31:20,880 --> 00:31:22,870
he'll go back to Seoul naturally.

411
00:31:24,730 --> 00:31:25,720
You two

412
00:31:25,970 --> 00:31:27,800
will have a perfect new year.

413
00:31:30,120 --> 00:31:31,200
Yes.

414
00:31:39,450 --> 00:31:40,510
Kim Haejun, right?

415
00:31:42,400 --> 00:31:44,800
Seems like my days
won't be boring anymore.

416
00:31:56,470 --> 00:32:09,920
[Tide of Love Season 2]

417
00:33:28,920 --> 00:33:33,920
[Tide of Love Season 2]
